insights.title: Andrej Karpathy: AGI is Still a Decade Away
insights.description: Karpathy states that AGI and fully autonomous AI agents won't arrive until around 2035, emphasizing that 'a decade of grunt work still lies ahead.' He revealed he hand-wrote 8,000 lines of code because AI agents 'didn't work well enough' for production use.
insights.author: Andrej Karpathy

insights.title: The AI Coding Backlash Has Arrived
insights.description: Growing developer frustration with AI coding tools, with viral 'AI Coding Sucks' content capturing widespread sentiment. 75% of developers still manually review every AI-generated code snippet, indicating significant trust issues with autonomous systems.
insights.author: Multiple Developers

insights.title: Replit's $3B Valuation and Agent 3 Launch
insights.description: Replit reached $3B valuation with $144M ARR after launching Agent 3, their most advanced autonomous programming agent that can test, debug, and work autonomously. CEO Amjad Masad is building for '1 billion developers worldwide.'
insights.author: Amjad Masad

insights.title: Simon Willison: Claude Code for Web Launch
insights.description: Anthropic launched Claude Code for web as an asynchronous coding agent, positioned as their answer to OpenAI's Codex. Willison provides detailed analysis of how he uses LLMs for coding assistance in both research and authoritarian phases.
insights.author: Simon Willison

insights.title: Stack Overflow Survey: AI Tool Sentiment Declining
insights.description: While 85% of developers regularly use AI tools, positive sentiment has decreased from 70%+ in 2023-2024 to just 60% in 2025. Professional developers show higher skepticism about AI coding tools compared to hobbyists.
insights.author: Stack Overflow

insights.title: Cursor vs GitHub Copilot: The New Leader in AI Coding
insights.description: Cursor has emerged as a strong challenger to GitHub Copilot, with Cursor 2.0 offering advanced agent modes and an AI-first interface. While Copilot integrates with multiple IDEs, Cursor's purpose-built environment appeals to developers wanting deeper AI integration.
insights.author: Industry Analysts

insights.title: DHH on AI: 'Vibe Coding' Risks Making Programmers Dumber
insights.description: David Heinemeier Hansson discusses how over-reliance on AI coding tools could make programmers 'dumber' if not balanced with maintaining fundamental coding skills. Emphasizes the importance of understanding code rather than just generating it.
insights.author: DHH (David Heinemeier Hansson)

insights.title: Hacker News: What AI Tool to Use for Coding in 2025?
insights.description: Active community discussion seeking recommendations for AI coding tools, indicating ongoing confusion about which tools provide the best value and capabilities. Shows developers are still evaluating optimal AI-assisted workflows.
insights.author: Hacker News Community

insights.title: Research: Fully Autonomous AI Agents Should Not Be Developed
insights.description: Academic research argues against developing fully autonomous AI agents, suggesting risks outweigh benefits for highly autonomous systems. Proposes evaluating AI agents on a sliding scale of autonomy rather than binary classification.
insights.author: Academic Researchers

insights.title: JetBrains Survey: 85% of Developers Use AI Tools
insights.description: The State of Developer Ecosystem 2025 report shows AI has become standard in developers' lives, with 85% regularly using AI tools and 62% relying on at least one AI tool daily. Indicates widespread adoption despite growing skepticism.
insights.author: JetBrains Research
